{
  "_about": "Authored lexicon for inferring a discipline on blank-discipline COCI staging courses. Applied by kb/_infer_disciplines.py over coci_minted_courses.json + coci_unified_courses.json. Every target discipline MUST be an exact string from reference/mq_disciplines.json (the apply script validates and refuses unknown targets). Assignments are written with discipline_source + discipline_confidence and are NEVER applied to entries that are human-reviewed (reviewed_at set) or present in coci_curation.json. STAGING + flagged-for-review — not ground truth. Edit this file and re-run the script to refine.",
  "_authored_by": "claude-opus-4-7 (discipline inference draft)",
  "_authored_at": "2026-05-22",
  "_revision_notes": "2026-05-22 pass 2: parent-first refinement. Added clean subject codes + cross-cutting title_keywords (foreign languages, music, electronics, drafting/CAD, culinary, AI, aviation, mortuary, HVAC, horticulture, solar, recreation). Keywords sidestep the fragmented/dirty subject codes (e.g. 'CUL ART', 'ELECTRN') by matching on title. 2026-05-22 pass 3: discipline-tail extension. Added 7 subject codes (ATHPE/ANAT/AGPS/PLS/AGRI/AODS/SWHS) + cross-cutting keywords (intercollegiate, yoga/pilates, anatomy/physiology, viticulture, addiction/substance-abuse, social-work/human-services, medical terminology, nutrition, film/cinema, sign language, court reporting, surgical, dental, machining, robotics, cybersecurity, floral, forestry, paramedic/EMS). Dropped 'ceramics' (studio art, not the industrial Ceramic Technology MQ discipline).",
  "_confidence": { "subject_map": 0.8, "title_keyword": 0.55 },
  "_policy": "subject_map: assign a discipline to ALL blank courses under a subject code whose sampled member titles are unambiguously one discipline (codes with mixed titles are deliberately omitted). title_keyword: lower-precision fallback for courses still blank after subject_map, matched on whole-word title tokens; kept to terms that are unambiguous on their own.",
